            "content": [
              {
                "type": "output_text",
                "text": "**AI** stands for **Artificial Intelligence**. It refers to the **simulation of human intelligence by machines**, especially computer systems. AI enables machines to perform tasks that typically require human intelligence, such as:\n\n- Understanding language (**NLP**)\n- Recognizing images and speech\n- Learning from experience (**machine learning**)\n- Making decisions and solving problems\n\n**Types of AI:**\n1. **Narrow AI**: Designed for specific tasks (e.g., Siri, self-driving cars).\n2. **General AI**: Theoretical AI that can perform any intellectual task a human can do.\n3. **Superintelligent AI**: A future concept where AI surpasses human intelligence.\n\n**Application areas:**\n- Virtual assistants (e.g., Alexa, Google Assistant)\n- Recommendation systems (e.g., Netflix, Amazon)\n- Robotics\n- Healthcare\n- Finance\n- Autonomous vehicles\n\n**In summary:**  \nAI is about making computers \"smart\" and able to mimic some aspects of human thinking and behavior.",
                "annotations": [],
                "logprobs": []
              }
            ],
